'''''Bossa Nova''''' is a [[2000]] [[romantic comedy]] [[film]] directed by [[Bruno Barreto]] dealing with several interwoven stories about people finding and losing love in [[Rio de Janeiro]].  The film stars [[Amy Irving]] (Barreto's wife and star of his earlier films ''[[A Show of Force]]'', ''[[Carried Away (film)|Carried Away]]'', and ''One Tough Cop'') as an [[English language]] teacher named Mary Ann.  


